Note that when we talk about ‘graph automorphisms’ we refer to the symmetries of a graph as a combinatorial object. By contrast, the ‘graph-induced symmetries’ are symmetries of dynamical systems induced by the properties of the underlying graph. The automorphism group of G and the group of graph-induced symmetries of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
