Graphons have been introduced as limit of convergent dense graph sequences; see [30] for details. Roughly speaking, a graph sequence is dense if the number of edges grows quadratically in the number of vertices. Convergence can be defined in terms of homomorphism densities (as we will not use this concept here, we refer to [30] for a definition): A dense graph sequence \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
