				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$(t(F, G_n))_n$$\end{document}(t(F,Gn))n is convergent. One of the main results of the theory is that for every convergent dense graph sequence there is a graphon (J, W) such that \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
