As a concrete example of symmetry-induced dynamically invariant subspace, consider the set of functions invariant under rotation along a fixed axis. Reduced dynamics can be represented as a graphon system parametrized by an interval, the rotation axis. Other examples are given by the finite subgroups of O(3), that is, the group of symmetries of the platonic solids.Fig. 7
